Business Brief -- Newmont Mining Corp.:
   Joint Venture Pact Signed
   With Ex-Soviet Republic
The company said the joint venture expects that the
stockpile would produce about 2.8 million ounces of gold, or
about $988.4 million at the current price, over the 20-year
life of the project, which is to begin in 1993. Newmont will
contribute the goldleaching technology it has developed for
low-grade ores to the project.
   Newmont said it is also exploring other possible
gold-mining projects in the republic.